$ WLAN - Wireless local area network
@ WLAN

WLAN refers to technologies and protocols that allow digital communication without wire (hence wireless).

→ development/networking/IEEE-802#ieee-802-11 refers to specific standard for WLAN, so IEEE 802.11 is a subset of WLAN, commonly referred to as WIFI.

{ WIFI #wifi

  In → Windows, the currently used WIFI profile seems to be stored under
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Microsoft/Windows/CurrentVersion/Control-Panel/Settings/Network/Preferences#reg-selected-wifi-profile[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Control Panel\Settings\Network\Preferences`, value SelectedWiFiProfile].

  See also → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Microsoft/Windows-NT/CurrentVersion/NetworkList/Profiles[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\NetworkList\Profiles`]

}

